Patrick Odey, Uyo Akwa Ibom State Government has granted amnesty to 68 inmates of the Nigeria Correctional Service in the state. A statement by the Controller, Nigeria Correctional Centre, Akwa Ibom State, Alex Oditah, said 22 of the inmates were pardoned from the Uyo Custodial Centre; 17 from Ikot Ekpene; another 17 from Eket Centre while 12 were freed from the Ikot Abasi Centre. The statement by the command’s Public Relations Officer, Ogbajie Ogbajie, on Wednesday said, “Based on the recommendation  from the Nigeria Correctional Service, Governor Udom Emmanuel has graciously pardoned the 68 inmates in four custodial centres across the state. “He admonished the released inmates to be of good conduct and never go back to crime,” the state commissioner for Justice and Attorney General, Uwemedimo Nwoko, who represented the governor said in the statement. Copyright PUNCH.
